{{unreferenced|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox settlement |name = Lara de los Infantes |settlement_type = town |image_skyline = |width = 300 |image_alt = |image_caption = |image_flag = |image_seal = |image_blank_emblem = |image_map = |mapsize = |map_alt = |map_caption = |pushpin_map = |pushpin_label_position = |pushpin_mapsize = |pushpin_map_caption = |subdivision_type = [[List of countries|Country]] |subdivision_name = [[Spain]] |subdivision_type1 = [[Autonomous communities of Spain|Autonomous community]] |subdivision_name1 = {{flagicon|Castile and León}} [[Castile and León]] |subdivision_type2 = [[Provinces of Spain|Province]] |subdivision_name2 = [[File:Flag Burgos Province.svg|20px|Flag of Burgos]] [[Burgos (province)|Burgos]] |subdivision_type3 = [[Comarca]] |subdivision_name3 = [[Sierra de la Demanda (comarca)|Sierra de la Demanda]] |subdivision_type4 = [[Municipality]] |subdivision_name4 = [[Jurisdicción de Lara]] |coordinates = |elevation_m = |area_total_km2 = |population_as_of = |population_total = |leader_title = |leader_name = |leader_party = |blank_name_sec1 = |blank_info_sec1 = |blank1_name_sec1 = |blank1_info_sec1 = |blank4_name = |blank4_info = |website = }}
'''Lara de los Infantes''' is a town with 26 inhabitants in the [[Burgos (province)|province of Burgos]] in the autonomous region of Castille y León in [[Spain]].
It is the seat of the [[municipality]] of [[Jurisdicción de Lara]], which includes a few more inhabitants as it includes other localities like [[Paúles de Lara]], and [[Aceña de Lara]]. It is situated in the shire of [[Sierra de la Demanda (shire)|Sierra de la Demanda]] 45 kilometers from the city of [[Burgos]].
Although sparsely populated today, the area was important in Roman times. In the Middle Ages it formed part of the Alfoz of Lara, where the [[Lara family]] had its hereditary base, and its full name, Lara de los Infante (Lara of the Princes) reflects that family's legend, told in the ''[[Cantar de los Siete Infantes de Lara]]''.
